    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Acid that occurs in sour milk as a thick water-soluble liquid. It is induced by bacterial decomposition of sugar, a process of fermentation; it may also be found in molasses, many fruits, beer and wine. Lactic acid is used in dyeing and leather processing. </Note_Text>
